## Quiz 4 ‚ÄĒ Diagnose the chain

Each is a verbal description of an MCMC chain. Name the failure mode (or say "healthy"). Possible answers: healthy, step too small, step too large, not converged, multimodal not crossed.

1. Trace plot looks like a flat fuzzy band; ACF drops to zero by lag 15; RŐā = 1.001. - Healthy, model looks converge
2. Trace plot is a slow upward walk over 4000 iterations; ACF is still ~0.7 at lag 100. - Unhealthy, model shows small decay, step too small, slow mixing, not converge, high autocorrelation
3. Trace plot is mostly flat but jumps wildly to a far value once every ~200 iterations and stays there briefly. Acceptance rate is 15%. - Unhealthy, Multimodal not crossed (or step too small)
4. Two chains start at őł = ‚ąí5 and +5 and after 1000 iterations they're still on opposite sides of zero, neither has crossed. - Unhealthy, not converge and the chain does not mix
5. Trace plot bounces in a tight band; ACF drops to zero by lag 5; acceptance rate is 95%. - Unhealthy, acceptance rate too high, step too small and slow mixing, the chain barely move

